          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three different targets were used for the proton",
                "backscattering yield measurements of C, N and Si.The",
                "targets having natural isotopic abundances, Ta-N on a",
                "carbon substrate, Au on a carbon foil and Au on Si-O(2)",
                "on Si were prepared by argon sputtering (Ta-N) and",
                "vacuum evaporation (Au foils). Each of the targets was",
                "first thoroughly investigated by He-4 backscattering",
                "to check the stoichiometries and layer thicknesses, to",
                "verify the homogeneity of the targets and to find",
                "possible interfering impurity elements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2SF HLS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Van de graaff accelerator of the",
                "university of helsinki."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Two methods of deriving the scattering cross sections",
                "from the experimental data were employed.",
                "For the thin layer targets, the ratio of the signal",
                "areas, were weighted by the known concentration ratio",
                "and ratio of the layer areal densities N(t),",
                "respectively, to obtain the cross section ratios.",
                "For the thick Si sample, a simulated computer fit",
                "provided the cross sections using of the dependence",
                "between the ion collision energy as a function of",
                "depth, stopping and scattering cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Computer data analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The experimental standard error of the present absolute",
                "cross section values is estimated to vary from 3-4% for",
                "carbon and silicon to 5% for nitrogen in the non-",
                "resonant energy regions. The relative accuracy for all",
                "elements is 2-3%. Near the narrow scattering anomaly of",
                "nitrogen at 1.74-MeV the cross section are more",
                "uncertain due to straggling and the finite target",
                "thickness and system resolution (12-KeV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
